Where would I change the icon of the collapsible with base-ui?
To change the icon of a collapsible component in Base UI, you would need to customize the `CollapsibleTrigger` component. Base UI allows for this kind of customization through render props or by providing custom components.

Here's how you might approach changing the icon in a Base UI collapsible:

```tsx
import * as React from 'react';
import { Collapsible, CollapsibleContent, CollapsibleTrigger } from '@radix-ui/react-collapsible';
// Import your custom icons
import { ChevronDownIcon, ChevronUpIcon } from 'your-icon-library'; // e.g., from Lucide, Heroicons, etc.

export function CustomCollapsible() {
  const [open, setOpen] = React.useState(false);

  return (
    <Collapsible 
      open={open} 
      onOpenChange={setOpen}
      className="w-full border rounded-md p-2"
    >
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
        <h3>Collapsible Title</h3>

        {/* Here's where you customize the icon */}
        <CollapsibleTrigger asChild>
          <button className="p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-100">
            {open ? (
              <ChevronUpIcon className="h-4 w-4" />
            ) : (
              <ChevronDownIcon className="h-4 w-4" />
            )}
          </button>
        </CollapsibleTrigger>
      </div>

      <CollapsibleContent className="pt-2">
        This is the collapsible content.
      </CollapsibleContent>
    </Collapsible>
  );
}
```

Key points:
1. You maintain state (`open`) to toggle between different icons
2. Use the `asChild` prop on `CollapsibleTrigger` to provide your own custom button
3. Conditionally render different icons based on the open/closed state

If you're using a specific library like Radix UI (which Base UI is built on), this approach allows you to completely replace the default icon with your custom one.

