How would I go about to change the width of the collapsible?
To change the width of the collapsible component, you have several options depending on how you want to implement it. Here are the main approaches:

### Option 1: Modify the CSS module for the Collapsible component

The most direct approach is to adjust the width in the Collapsible's own CSS module file:

1. Open `next-base-test/src/app/components/Collapsible/Collapsible.module.css`
2. Find the `.Collapsible` class or add a width property to it:

```css
/* In Collapsible.module.css */
.Collapsible {
  width: 400px; /* Set your desired width */
  /* or */
  max-width: 90%; /* Responsive width */
  /* other existing styles */
}
```

### Option 2: Create a custom width prop for the component

You can modify your `ExampleCollapsible` component to accept a width prop:

```tsx
// In next-base-test/src/app/components/Collapsible/Collapsible.tsx
"use client";

