Why is my collapsible narrow when collapsed, and wide when opened?
After examining your CSS files, I can see the issue causing your collapsible to be narrow when collapsed and wide when opened. The main problems are:

### Main Issues

1. **Missing Width in Panel**: Your `.Panel` class has a defined height but is missing a clear width definition when collapsed.

2. **Transition Property**: Your `.Panel` class uses `transition: all 150ms ease-out;` which means ALL properties are transitioning, not just the height.

3. **Content Overflow**: When collapsed, the content isn't visible so it doesn't push the width, but when opened, the content may be wider, causing expansion.

### Solutions

Here's how to fix it:

```css
/* Update your .Panel class in Collapsible.module.css */
.Panel {
    display: flex;
    width: 100%; /* Add this to ensure consistent width */
    height: var(--collapsible-panel-height);
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: end;
    overflow: hidden;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.25rem;
    transition: height 150ms ease-out; /* ONLY transition height, not all properties */

    &[data-starting-style],
    &[data-ending-style] {
        height: 0;
        width: 100%; /* Ensure width is consistent even when height is 0 */
    }
}

/* Update your .Content class to ensure consistent width */
.Content {
    display: flex;
    width: 100%; /* Add this to ensure consistent width */
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    background-color: var(--color-gray-100);
    cursor: text;
    box-sizing: border-box; /* Add this to include padding in width calculation */
}
```

### Key Changes

1. **Add explicit width: 100%** to the `.Panel` class
2. **Change transition to only affect height**, not all properties
3. **Add width: 100%** to the collapsed state as well
4. **Add width: 100%** to the `.Content` class
5. **Add box-sizing: border-box** to ensure padding doesn't increase the effective width

These changes will ensure that your collapsible maintains the same width whether it's open or closed, creating a more consistent visual experience.

### Additional Recommendation

You might want to set an explicit width for your collapsible container in your page layout to ensure consistent sizing across all states:

```tsx
